{"parse":{"title":"British Association for Local History","pageid":13502282,"revid":780523655,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>British Association for Local History</b> (BALH) is a membership organisation that exists to promote the advancement of public education through the study of <a href=\"/wiki/Local_history\" title=\"Local history\">local history</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-CCframework_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CCframework-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  and to encourage and assist the study of local history throughout <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Britain\" title=\"Great Britain\">Great Britain</a> as an academic discipline and as a leisure activity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>BALH was founded and registered as a <a href=\"/wiki/Charitable_organization#England_and_Wales\" title=\"Charitable organization\">charity</a> in England and Wales on 30 September 1982<sup id=\"cite_ref-CCframework_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CCframework-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> through an initiative by the National Council of Social Services (now the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Council_for_Voluntary_Organisations\" title=\"National Council for Voluntary Organisations\">National Council for Voluntary Organisations</a>) to bring together the work of previously separate organisations in the field.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HTcavendish-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> It aims to be the national umbrella organisation for the subject and many local history societies and groups are members of BALH, though others remain outside.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HTcavendish-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> People with an interest in local history can also join BALH as individual members.\n</p><p>BALH's activities include the publication of the quarterly journal <i>The Local Historian</i> (first published in 1952), a quarterly magazine <i>Local History News</i>, a quarterly e-newsletter, as well as a number of books and pamphlets on the topic.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BALHabout_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BALHabout-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> It also organises an annual lecture, national and regional conferences and guided visits to libraries, museums<sup id=\"cite_ref-BALHabout_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BALHabout-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and institutions such as <a href=\"/wiki/The_National_Archives_(United_Kingdom)\" title=\"The National Archives (United Kingdom)\">The National Archives</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/College_of_Arms\" title=\"College of Arms\">College of Arms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HTcavendish-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The Association also coordinates an annual Local History Day.\n</p><p>The British Association for Local History also has an education committee that has been active in lobbying the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Curriculum_Council\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Curriculum Council\">National Curriculum Council</a> to increase the teaching of local history in schools, as well as in preparing courses and publications for teachers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HTcavendish-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Association's president is Professor <a href=\"/wiki/Caroline_Barron\" title=\"Caroline Barron\">Caroline Barron</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Holloway,_University_of_London\" title=\"Royal Holloway, University of London\">Royal Holloway, University of London</a>. The announcement was made at the Association's Local History Day in June 2016.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BALHnews_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BALHnews-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> She replaced <a href=\"/wiki/David_Hey\" title=\"David Hey\">David Hey</a> as President, who died in February 2016.\n</p><p>The administrative address for the Association is in Macclesfield, Cheshire.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=British_Association_for_Local_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Historiography_of_the_United_Kingdom\" title=\"Historiography of the United Kingdom\">Historiography of the United Kingdom</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Alan_Ball_Local_History_Awards\" title=\"Alan Ball Local History Awards\">Alan Ball Local History Awards</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Geographical_Association\" title=\"Geographical Association\">Geographical Association</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=British_Association_for_Local_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-CCframework-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-CCframework_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-CCframework_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.charity-commission.gov.uk/Showcharity/RegisterOfCharities/CharityFramework.aspx?RegisteredCharityNumber=285467&amp;SubsidiaryNumber=0\">Charity framework</a> Charity Commission, accessed 2012-05-08</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.balh.co.uk/index.php\">British Association for Local History</a>, accessed 2012-05-08</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-HTcavendish-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-HTcavendish_3-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.historytoday.com/richard-cavendish/british-association-local-history\">British Association for Local History</a> History Today, accessed 2012-05-08</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-BALHabout-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-BALHabout_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-BALHabout_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.balh.org.uk/about\">About BALH</a>, accessed 2016-09-06</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-BALHnews-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-BALHnews_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.balh.org.uk/news/new-president-announced\">New President Announced | BALH News</a>, accessed 2016-06-06</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=British_Association_for_Local_History&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.balh.org.uk/\">British Association for Local History website</a></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role